<br>
So if it's correct that the guilds who get there first make up the rules so that they can play nice with each other while the rest of us build up our guilds to even get to their level, don't you think that they should submit their agreements to the community? Don't you think all players should be able to reference these agreements as opposed to players from 20 guilds sending Karadin, Kenshiiro, Brotor or the Pope a /tell asking them to explain the agreements of the mobs in HoT while they are pulling AoW?<br>
<br>
Then this agreement issue gets me thinking ...what if BoTS tells TL here's the agreement on AoW--You can't kill him unless you pay us 100k each time you kill the giant with the purple hat and if you don't pay us then you can't be on the rotation. Is NB, FK, LOL and LOM going to have to pay BoTS, too when they break the rotation?<br>
<br>
So I ask you, why doesn't the community as a whole get representatives to review these made up policies? <p><p style="line-height: 100%"><font face="Papyrus"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=189879"target="_blank"><b>Keranee Pureheart
