</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uborick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 1:56:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rotation Rules</span><hr size=1> Keranee,<br>
<br>
There's no need to open the rotations up for general discussion because the rotation guidelines are based for the most part on common sense:  Kill the mob and join the club.  When the mob spawns on your turn you have 24 hours to kill the mob or pass to the next guild.  If you do not kill within that time, your turn passes to the next guild.  If a patch is declared, then the RTA reps will agree to have 'FFA' days as required. <br>
<br>
It's simple.  Your '10000 plat' analogy just isn't going to happen.<br>
<br>
Now, there -are- a few exceptions to the above rules.  These exceptions were not made just to suit us. They were made because the situations require exceptions.  An example of these exceptions are NTOV and the Dozekar rotation.<br>
<br>
You see, before Verant put in the random spawn code it wasn't an issue.  The drakes all spawned at the same time and if you didn't kill the drakes then nobody was to blame but you.  Now, however, each of the drakes is on a random spawn timer, and so we have to use common sense and WAIT until all of the drakes are up to kill them.  <br>
<br>
Why should Noble Blade tell BOTS/Tindi what their Blood rotation should be like?  When Noble Blade kills Blood, if we have a problem with the rotation THEN we will have earned the right to discuss it with the people who DO kill the mob.<br>
<br>
If you don't kill the mob, then what does it matter if you don't have a say in how the rotation goes?  If you kill the mob, you DO have input.<br>
<br>
Now, some bright person is going to say, 'But Borick, if we don't have a say in the rotation, why should we bother about YOUR drakes?  We're not on the rotation, so we're not bound by your rules.'  And you would be right.  If you're not on the rotation, then you can kill all the named drakes that you want and all we can do is bitch...  until the day comes when you want to be on a rotation and expect fair treatment from us.  <br>
<br>
The rotation system protects everyone, even the guilds that are not on the rotations.  It gives these guilds a chance to see mobs they might otherwise never see.  Snub the RTA if you will, but the day will come when you desire a fair shot at a mob, and the rotation guilds will remember your behavior.<br>
<br>
Borick Ascid<br>
High Priest of Brell<br>
Noble Blade<br>
The Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kenshiiro>Kenshiiro </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shadows of Yamabushi</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 2:19:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re</span><hr size=1> Gromm,<br>
